article.headline: Manhattan 82, Niagara 81 (OT)
article.story: LEWISTON, N.Y. (AP) -- Jason Wingate hit two free throws with 18.6 seconds left in overtime to lift Manhattan to an 82-81 win over Niagara on Monday night. Wingate finished with 21 points and eight assists for the Jaspers (16-8, 12-4 Metro Atlantic Athletic), who rallied from a seven-point deficit in overtime after squandering a 17-point lead in the second half. Jeff Xavier had 21 points and 13 rebounds for Manhattan, while Arturo Dubois also had 21 points. Mike Konovelchick finished with 12 points. Niagara's Clif Brown had 28 points to go along with 12 rebounds for his fifth double-double of the season. Barry Durosier had 16 points off the bench for the Purple Eagles (10-14, 7-9), but it was his turnover that allowed Manhattan to get back into the game. The Purple Eagles were up 79-74 with 1:11 remaining in overtime when Durosier was called for traveling for running along the baseline while trying to inbound the ball. Wingate then hit a 3-pointer to pull Manhattan to within two points. J.R. Duffey and Lorenzo Miles added 14 points apiece for Niagara.
